This repository contains NO personal data, NO real microdata, and NO real tax returns.
Synthetic fixtures are generated from a deterministic seed and distributed under CC0-1.0.
Legislative-parameter data are curated annotations of public statutes (SFS) and are
distributed under EUPL-1.2.

Third-party dependencies are listed in pyproject.toml and uv.lock. Each dependency
is subject to its own licence; all are EUPL-1.2 compatible as documented in
docs/eu-compliance.md.

This software was developed as part of a twenty-project research portfolio on income,
wealth, taxation, inequality, and intergenerational mobility in Sweden, commissioned
by the Department of Economics at Stockholm University.
